Rating: 4
Awesome, but I made some changes. 1) I cooked it (up until the bread) a few days in advance. I wanted the discordant flavors to blend; 2) I substituted persimmons for the pears, figs for the prunes, dried cherries for the cranberries, and added the seeds of one pomegranate; 3) I used Viognier for it's creaminess; 4) I added chicken stock; and 5) I added 1# chopped chicken and sauteed chicken livers. This helped give it a depth and richness I thought the original lacked. The result reminded me a bit of my grand aunt's mincemeat pies, and a bit of a fig pate.

